main event: An unidentified foreign object was observed near Kansas City, Missouri, displaying a brilliant shooting star phenomenon and high-speed vertical trajectory.
interesting points: The object was tracked by radar and showed a maximum velocity of 600-750 knots,The observation lasted for approximately 30 seconds,The object underwent a burnout on a vertical axis,The radar tracking indicated the object varied its speed considerably,The maximum estimated speed of descent was approximately 30,000 mph.
witness description: Walter C. Halloran, Capt., USAF, acting as a magnetic sensing operator.
